title: GoTo Jumps in Trading Debut After Indonesian Tech Giant’s IPO Raises $1.1 Billion
sub_head: The IPO is one of the world’s largest so far this year
body:
Shares of Indonesia-based GoTo Group jumped in their public trading debut on Monday, catapulting the ride-hailing, e-commerce and financial services company into the ranks of the country’s most valuable stocks.
GoTo soared as much as 23% above its initial public offering price in early trading on the Indonesia Stock Exchange. Shares closed 13% higher, giving the company a market capitalization equivalent to more than $30 billion.
